---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Matthew D. Regele | Associate Professor & Director of Assessment"
  description="Academic website of Matthew D. Regele, Associate Professor of Management & Entrepreneurship and Director of Assessment at Xavier University's Williams College of Business."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 mb-16">
    <img
      src="/images/headshot.png"
      alt="Matthew D. Regele"
      class="w-40 h-40 rounded-full object-cover shadow-lg ring-4 ring-navy-100"
    />
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">Matthew D. Regele</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-1">
        Associate Professor of Management &amp; Entrepreneurship
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-1">
        Director of Assessment, Williams College of Business
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-500">Xavier University &middot; Cincinnati, OH</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gold-600 mt-3 italic">
        Studying how narratives about purpose, power, and profit shape strategy, careers, and venture outcomes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-4">About</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        My research examines how the stories organizations tell about purpose, power, and profit
        shape strategic choices, individual careers, and venture outcomes. Across a range of
        settings, I study how these narratives become embedded in governance structures, incentive
        systems, and everyday work practices â€” and how they ultimately determine who bears risk and
        who captures value.
      </p>
      <p>
        I rely on qualitative approaches including ethnography, interviews, archival research, and
        netnography to surface the mechanisms that connect narrative to organizational design and
        performance. My work sits at the intersection of strategy, entrepreneurship, and sociology,
        contributing to research on venture legitimacy, labor markets, organizational purpose, and
        entrepreneurial careers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Alongside my academic work, I serve as Chief Operating Officer of Habit Technology, LLC,
        where I am actively engaged in the challenges of early-stage venture development. I view
        practice as a testing ground for ideas about incentives, governance, and strategic choice
        that also inform my teaching and research.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Education -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-6">Education</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1 sm:gap-4">
        <span class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 sm:w-56 shrink-0">Yale University</span>
        <span class="text-slate-700">Ph.D., Organizations &amp; Management, 2018</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1 sm:gap-4">
        <span class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 sm:w-56 shrink-0">Babson College</span>
        <span class="text-slate-700">MBA, <em>summa cum laude</em>, 2012</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1 sm:gap-4">
        <span class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 sm:w-56 shrink-0">Bowdoin College</span>
        <span class="text-slate-700">AB, Economics, 2006</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1 sm:gap-4">
        <span class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 sm:w-56 shrink-0">London School of Economics</span>
        <span class="text-slate-700">The General Course, 2005</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Links -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-6">Explore</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <a href="/research" class="group block bg-navy-50 rounded-lg p-6 hover:bg-navy-100 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 group-hover:text-navy-600 mb-2">Research</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Publications, working papers, and active projects across entrepreneurship and strategy.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/teaching" class="group block bg-navy-50 rounded-lg p-6 hover:bg-navy-100 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 group-hover:text-navy-600 mb-2">Teaching</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Courses in entrepreneurship, management, and strategy at undergraduate and MBA levels.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog" class="group block bg-navy-50 rounded-lg p-6 hover:bg-navy-100 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-serif font-bold text-navy-800 group-hover:text-navy-600 mb-2">Blog</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Reflections on research, teaching, and organizational life.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
